ma-hartüñ§:

Step 1 ‚Äì Rapid Verdict
Your JS classes are üí™ ‚Äï airtight crypto, queue-managed API calls, and session tooling look solid. The backend proxy is clean, CORS+helmet+rate-limit on point. So the core logic isn‚Äôt the reason the UI buttons feel dead.

Step 2 ‚Äì Top 5 Likely Blockers

Missing element IDs ‚Äì If any of these IDs (send-message-button, start-button, etc.) aren‚Äôt in the HTML, every listener silently fails.

file:// origin quirk ‚Äì Browsers don‚Äôt actually send an Origin header for file://, so your proxy‚Äôs CORS rule isn‚Äôt hit. Solution: serve the page via npx serve or python -m http.server on localhost.

Crypto-subtle needs HTTPS ‚Äì Chrome blocks AES-GCM from an unsecured origin. Same fix as #2.

API key masking ‚Äì After you save, the <input> is filled with dots (actual value gone). Next save attempt overwrites with the dots string, failing validation. Either keep the real value in memory or disable subsequent saves.

Event flow race ‚Äì DOMContentLoaded fires before your script tag if the code is in an external file added at the very end? ‚úîÔ∏è Fine. But if you pasted inside the HTML after the listeners, wrap it in defer or type="module".

Step 3 ‚Äì Immediate Patches

