‚öñÔ∏è 11-Point Scorecard ‚Äî Current ‚Äúinline-script‚Äù build
(0 = üöÆ unusable ‚Äî 10 = üöÄ enterprise-grade)

#	Benchmark	Score	Quick Rationale
1	Security	7.5	AES-GCM client crypto ‚úîÔ∏é, key never leaves RAM ‚ûï. CORS still allows file:// (should be trimmed) and no strict CSP / COOP headers ‚ûñ.
2	Reliability / Error-handling	7	Proxy forwards OpenAI errors; frontend wraps most awaits in try/catch. Still in-memory queues & session loss on refresh ‚ûñ.
3	Scalability	6	Throttle (350 ms) avoids rate limits; context window cap. Single Node process, no worker threads / queue persistence ‚ûñ.
4	Developer DX	7.5	Simple npm start, minimal deps; but giant inline script, no hot-reload, no linter / tests yet.
5	Token Efficiency	8	History trimmed, summarising prompt, no duplicate payloads. No streaming / auto-compression yet.
6	Modularity / Code Structure	5.5	Classes are nice, but everything still lives in one <script> block ‚Äî hard to navigate & test.
7	Performance	7	Non-blocking defer (if added), crypto in browser, minimal bundle. 350 ms queue introduces latency; no HTTP/2 / gzip yet.
8	UX / UI Feedback	7	Thinking dots, notifications, metrics panel üëç. Desktop-only CSS, no dark-mode / mobile responsiveness.
9	Maintainability	6.5	Good naming & comments; but no docs, Storybook, ADRs or unit tests. Inline code is brittle for PR reviews.
10	Deployment Readiness	6.5	Works on localhost; proxy uses helmet & rate-limit. No .env, no CI/CD, no container / IaC script.
11	MacBook M2 Footprint	9	Zero Docker, light deps, browser crypto ‚Äî runs cool & fast on Apple Silicon.
Overall ‚âà 7.0 / 10 ‚Üí Solid MVP
Secure, functional, and lightweight, but to hit ‚Äú11/10‚Äù everywhere you still need the upgrades we sketched earlier: split into ES modules, add .env + nodemon, move sessions to a real store, tighten CORS & CSP, add CI/tests, enable streaming & summarisation, etc.

